problem_text:
The power output of a laser is measured in units of watts (W), where one watt is equal to one joule per second. $\left(1 \mathrm{~W}=1 \mathrm{~J} \cdot \mathrm{s}^{-1}\right.$.) What is the number of photons emitted per second by a $1.00 \mathrm{~mW}$ nitrogen laser? The wavelength emitted by a nitrogen laser is $337 \mathrm{~nm}$.The unit of answer should be  $
10^{15} \text { photon } \cdot \mathrm{s}^{-1}
$

